column1: Table Title: Central Provident Fund Contributions, Withdrawals And Amount Due To Members, Monthly
Home Ownership Scheme Using Central Provident Fund
Reached 55 Years Of Age And Above
Contributions (Net Of Refunds) By Members (Million Dollars):
Contributions include dividends from Special Discounted Shares and Government Grants.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members (Million Dollars):
Withdrawals include transfers to / from Reserve Account / general moneys of the Fund.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Home Ownership Scheme Using Central Provident Fund -> Housing Schemes - Public Housing (Million Dollars):
Refer to net amount withdrawn (gross amount withdrawn less amount refunded) by members.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Home Ownership Scheme Using Central Provident Fund -> Housing Schemes - Private Housing (Million Dollars):
Refer to net amount withdrawn (gross amount withdrawn less amount refunded) by members.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Reached 55 Years Of Age And Above (Million Dollars):

Includes first and subsequent withdrawals.  1995 increase was due to withdrawals of government cash grant under Share Ownership Top-up Scheme II and CPF top-up scheme.  2000 & 2001 increase was due to withdrawals of government CPF top-up scheme.  2003 & 2004 increase was due to withdrawals of the economic restructuring shares and relaxation of withdrawal rule from once in 3 years to annually.  2005 & 2006 increase was due to withdrawals of government top-ups & sale proceeds from their Singtel shares.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Leaving Singapore & Malaysia Permanently (Million Dollars):
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Medisave Scheme (Million Dollars):
Prior to 2003, figures include private medical scheme and Eldershield scheme.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Private Medical Insurance Scheme (Million Dollars):
Prior to 2003, figures are included in Medisave scheme.
Withdrawals (Net Of Refunds) By Members -> Others (Million Dollars):

Includes withdrawals under Home Protection Insurance, Retirement Sum (previously known as Minimum Sum), Dependants' Protection Insurance, Education, MediShield Life (previously known as Medishield), ElderShield, CareShield Life, Lifelong Income, Non-residential Properties, Investment and Special Discounted Shares schemes, transfers to/from Reserve Account/general moneys of the Fund and on grounds of reduced life expectancy.
na   not available or not applicable
-     nil or negligible or not significant
Numbers may not add up to the totals due to rounding.
Data are the latest available at the time of access or download. Some statistics, particularly those for the most recent time periods, are provisional and may be subject to revision at a later date.
Values are shown in Singapore dollars (unless otherwise specified).
